YES !<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Are the Kunark dragons supposed to be pushovers compared to Velious dragons?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
YES !<br>
<br>
Haven't you read any of the game lore at all? Yes, the kunark dragons were &quot;impatient youths&quot;. Younger and less experienced means *weaker*. Vox and Naggy were also called &quot;young&quot;.<br>
<br>
Edit: Just to elaborate, think about the dragons in WW, many of these are far weaker than the Kunark dragons. Some of them are weaker than Vox and Naggy. Should they boost all of these dragons up to NToV level? If you paid any attention to the game lore you would know that they are &quot;young&quot; dragons and are SUPPOSED to be weaker.<br>
<br>
