As I see it, with each expansion, they've raised the advancement for the entire game. We've got another expansion coming out in October or November, which is most likely going to knock the high end game up another notch or two. that means those in power now will be racing again to be the most powerful in PoP.<br>
<br>
Here's the biggest flaw with EQ; Levels are crippling the high end game. You have a smooth slope from level 1 to level 50, and then you run into a mountain when you hit 51.<br>
When you finally make level 60, you can then grind out AA points left and right, and still hunt the same creatures as before, which is competition for players that aren't 60, and aren't grinding AA exp.<br>
<br>
It's basically SOE forcing highly advanced characters to farm exp with less advanced players. The game is designed to separate players by the level system, and because of the level cap, there's a huge bottleneck forming.<br>
<br>
Did you guys know that a player with 256 AA points (max AA available) has ground enough experience to be the equivilent of a level 120+ player? And yet that person is still level 60, and still using level 60 spells, and still hunting in places with lower EXP and AA skilled players.<br>
<br>
The only way to fix this is to change the current EXP system from level 51-60 to cover level 51-100+ instead. This separates the advanced characters, and allows SOE to balance encounters for more specified players.<br>
<br>
They could implement this fairly easily. Basically the exp needed to go from 51 to 60 would be averaged out to cover level 51 to 100. Players would automatically ding multiple times to make up for the difference, and all would be fine.<br>
<br>
It would still take the same amount of experience to get to the high level game, it would just be more levels, and more room to separate the high end game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unecamus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>necamus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/9/02 9:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> exp</span><hr size=1> all the game needs is more zones for upper lvls to get exp/ aa pts =) there is like 5 great zones that always have 60+ppl.  should just fix some other zones for 55+ so u can go to a zone and get a group/solo with 20-30ppl in it.<br>
